			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4334207">
									

<p>The primary issue with non-standard Classification Systems (like Threat Levels) was how incredibly vague they are. These two new classification systems have very set, defined definitions that leave little up to interpretation (much like object classes/containment classes already do.)</p>
<p>They are obviously not required but they can make for some narrative interest to an SCP much like Object Classes already do.</p>
<p>Besides that, I think Kaktus justified their existence in-universe quite well.</p>

