														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4334203">
									

<p>This conceptual expansion is large enough that I'd feel the need to refer back to this page every time I saw the format just to be sure that I'm understanding it right in each context. I'm not really in favor of that, since object classes are normally just shorthand expectation setters (and occasionally plot points), and this puts a lot of extra weight there. That's effectively just a readability vs. realism tradeoff, and I don't know if any changes would actually address it, but I do think articles that don't take that into account during the writing process may end up slightly worse off because of it.</p>
<p>That said, more power to everyone to experiment, etc. etc.</p>

