					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/more-power" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5054156); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=5054156&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610252343" alt="More Power" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=5054156)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/more-power" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5054156); return false;" >More Power</a></span> <span class="odate time_1566181575 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">19 Aug 2019 02:26</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4334246">
									

<p>There are a number of issues with this. The writing itself is not the problem, mind you; Kaktus did a good job with making this seem like an in-universe article. However, there are a number of things that bug me.</p>
<ol>
<li>Thaumiel is <strong>not</strong> an esoteric class. Considering it has its own tag, lumping it together with the rest of the esoteric classes just feels off.</li>
<li>Basically what <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/pedantique" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3118444); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3118444&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1566181618" alt="Pedantique" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3118444)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/pedantique" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3118444); return false;">Pedantique</a></span> said about the Disruption and Risk classes. They make thing more complicated; and we already have Threat Levels, which are pretty clear at what they mean.</li>
</ol>
<p>These two points, along with some other minor ones, give this my downvote.<br />
Again, downvoting for the component aspect, not the writing about it.</p>

							</div>

								
