			<div class="content" id="post-content-4334257">
									

<p>It's not unreasonable to consider thaumiel an esoteric class, even if it has its own tag. Off of nearly ~4700 as of writing, only about ~100 are thaumiel. It's fairly uncommon and I think that justifies it as esoteric, even if you ignore the no-canon aspect of this.</p>
<p>And yeah Threat Levels are <em>very</em> unclear for the reader if you don't have them memorized. This has a leg up on them on account of integrating a simple 1 to 5 scale that should make it easy even if you don't remember them all - you just need to know it's a one to five scale rather than remembering a shitton of colors.</p>

