<ol>
<li>It's a &quot;Containment Class&quot;, and Thaumiel says nothing about difficulty of containment. Some are trivial to contain and would be Safe otherwise, while others might be Keter.</li>
<li>Threat Levels are <em>not</em> clear in what they mean, which is their primary weakness. Additionally they are too similar to the conception of object classes to be orthogonal to them; there's literally a &quot;Threat Level: White&quot; which is the same as Thaumiel. SCP-3000 is Thaumiel but it's definitely not harmless.</li>
