<p>(Vlam and Keneq both being words for fire and Ekhi and Amida both being associated with the sun)</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Vlam means <strong>flame</strong> and Keneq means <strong>fire.</strong> One refers to a fire no larger than a match/candle flame. The other refers to a large fire, think a camp fire.</p>
<p>Ekhi does mean sun, yes, but Amida does not have any relation to the sun at all. It means &quot;Infinite Light.&quot;</p>
<blockquote>
<p>then it's done it in the most roundabout and nonsensical way possible.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>How so? You're being quite vague.</p>

